developer_response.body:
To cope with nausea - please consider the following:
- Adjust "Dynamic Comfort mode" bar in the settings and set it to the max; 
- In our experience, motion sickness ceases to be a problem relatively quickly if you give yourself and the game a chance;
- During the adjustment period - try to limit your gaming sessions in VR. Make them shorter, even if more frequent than usual;
- It has been proved that chewing gum reduces visually induced motion sickness: https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00221-021-06303-5
- Try playing with a fan facing you in the same room as you play.

Please check the "Basic Flight" section in the Tutorial, on the right monitor at the base, it will help you learn the basics. 

It is also worth taking a look at the Flight Setup settings, available at the bottom of the central monitor, a moment before starting the mission - there you can change the flight model to one closer to simulation, or a simplified one (Arcade), and modify the sensitivity of your machine. 

It may also be helpful to visit the "Controls" section (left monitor at the base), where you can choose the Controls Layout that is convenient for you.

Give yourself a chance and take a few minutes to practice, and you'll turn into an excellent pilot in no time!

If you'd like to take another try - please consider the following:
- Adjust "Dynamic Comfort mode" bar in the settings and set it to the max; 
- In our experience, motion sickness ceases to be a problem relatively quickly if you give yourself and the game a chance;
- During the adjustment period - try to limit your gaming sessions in VR. Make them shorter, even if more frequent than usual;
- It has been proved that chewing gum reduces visually induced motion sickness: https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00221-021-06303-5
- Try playing with a fan facing you in the same room as you play.
